media tags
----------
there are 4 types 
+ image
+ audio 
+ video
+ iframe

1. image tag:- it is used to add images. it is a unpaired tag.
    attributes:- src, alt, heght, width
    syntax:- <img src="" alt="" height="" width="">

2. audio tag:- it is used to add audio file to a webpage
    attributes:- src, controls, muted, autoplay, loop.
   + here autoplay will not work.
   + src --> this is the source where we insert the audio path.  we can't able to add absolute path because of copyrights.  we can add relative path.
   + control --> if we want to have play, pause, mute we need this attribute.  without control we can't able to see anything.
   + muted --> used to mute the audio.
   syntax:- <audio src="" controls muted autoplay loop>


video
-----
video tag is used to insert a video to a webpage. if we want to use auto play attribute we need to use muted compulsary.

attributes:- src, controls, muted, autoplay, loop, height, width.
syntax:- <video src="" controls muted autoplay loop height="px" width="px">


iframe
------
it is used to embed a webpage inside another webpage.
here we can embed only maps or videos.


step1:- open youtube video, click share button.
step2:- click on embed or copy unique id then paste it in src.
step3:- copy the html code.

syntax:- <ifrane src="" frameborder="">



semantic tags
-------------
- the tags which describes itself to the browser and to the developer is called as semantic tags.
- it is implemented in HTML 5.

why semantic tags
-----------------
due to the drawback of olden days web pages development  that is using only div tag they are implemented semantic tags.

example:-
+----------------------------------+
|             HEADER               |
+----------------------------------+
|               NAV                |
+----------------------------------+
|               MAIN               |
|   +-----------+   +-----------+  |
|   |  SECTION  |   |  ASIDE    |  |
|   +-----------+   +-----------+  |
|   |           ARTICLE         |  |
+----------------------------------+
|             FOOTER               |
+----------------------------------+




difference between HTML and HTML5

HTML
------
 + semantic tags are not implemented.
 + media tags are not fully supported.
 + limited browser supported for HTML.
 + JavaScript is partially supported.

HTML5
------
+ semantic tags are implemented.
+ media tags are supported.
+ all browsers supported.
+ Javascript is full supported.
